  <front>
   <head>To a Gentleman, who shew'd a fine Poem as his own.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">more at Criticks, , repine,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who say those Numbers are not thine.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I own I was suspicious too,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And thought the Verse too good for :</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But since  those Lines you writ,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Proof is full, and I submit.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">So, if  should profess,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">She owes Herself her glorious Dress;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And , Empress of the Night,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Declare she shines by native Light;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">(Tho' envious Criticks vent their Gall,)</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8" />
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
